<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="iddd06a648-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee" identifier="/us/usc/t2/s2141"><num value="2141">§ 2141.</num><heading> Supervision of Botanic Garden</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The supervision of the Capitol police shall extend over the Botanical Garden.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="iddd06a649-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee">(R.S. § 1826.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="iddd06a64a-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="iddd06a64b-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="iddd06a64c-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was classified to section 215 of former Title 40, prior to the enactment of Title 40, Public Buildings, Property, and Works, by <ref href="/us/pl/107/217/s1">Pub. L. 107–217, § 1</ref>, <date date="2002-08-21">Aug. 21, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1062">116 Stat. 1062</ref>.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">R.S. § 1826 derived from Res. <date date="1870-07-15">July 15, 1870</date>, No. 131, <ref href="/us/stat/16/391">16 Stat. 391</ref>.</p>
</note>
